  "interpretation": {
    "what_it_means": "Simple voting classifier achieves 50.76% on holdout \u2014 barely above chance. But per-feature win rates show real directional signals consistent with the logistic regression: questions lose (38.7% win rate vs 61.3% for non-question), exclamation marks lose (39.0%), 'why' questions lose (40.9%), while 'actually' wins (64.7%), 'never' wins (57.9%), and imperative verbs win (58.2%).",
    "what_it_does_NOT_mean": "The simple voting model is not useful as a ranker. The per-feature lifts are informative but shouldn't be applied as rigid rules \u2014 they reflect Upworthy's 2013-2015 clickbait domain, not YouTube documentary titles."
  },
